<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;line-height:150%'><b><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>ABSTRACT<o:p></o:p></span></b=
></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;line-height:150%'><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>FashionConnect is a comprehen=
sive
web-based platform designed to address the specific challenges faced by loc=
al
fashion designers in Malawi. The current reliance on general social media
platforms for business operations presents limitations in terms of secure
payments, trust verification, custom order management, and effective product
discovery. This project develops a specialized platform that offers verified
designer profiles, integrated local payment methods, vector-based product
search, and structured communication tools. The system aims to formalize
fashion businesses while creating a trusted marketplace that benefits both
designers and customers through tailored e-commerce functionality and secure
transactions.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

