<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;line-height:150%'><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The fashion industry in Malawi
represents a significant sector within the creative economy with considerab=
le
growth potential as identified in the National Export Strategy II (2021-202=
6).
Currently, local fashion designers primarily operate through informal chann=
els
and general social media platforms such as Facebook and Instagram. While th=
ese
platforms provide visibility to potential customers, they fundamentally lack
specialized tools necessary for fashion business transactions, secure payme=
nts,
and effective order management. Research conducted by the Ministry of Trade=
 and
Industry (2021) indicates that 78% of fashion entrepreneurs in Malawi use
social media as their primary business platform despite experiencing
significant operational challenges. These platforms were created for social
interaction rather than commerce, leaving critical gaps in functionality
specific to fashion businesses. For designers, this translates to manual
tracking of orders, insecure payment collection, and difficulties maintaini=
ng
professional client relationships. The fashion ecosystem in Malawi consists
primarily of independent designers, small scale production studios, and a
growing consumer base interested in local designs. However, the lack of
structured digital infrastructure creates barriers to growth, formalization,
and market expansion. Current digital solutions either come from internatio=
nal
platforms with prohibitive fees and foreign payment requirements or rudimen=
tary
local websites lacking essential fashion-specific functionality. FashionCon=
nect
addresses these challenges by creating a specialized platform built
specifically for the needs of Malawi's fashion industry. The system integra=
tes
local payment methods, provides tools for portfolio management and custom
ordering, and establishes trust mechanisms that benefit both designers and =
clients.
This aligns with national priorities for digital transformation in key sect=
ors
while addressing the specific operational needs of creative entrepreneurs.<=
o:p></o:p></span></p>

